      <section eId="sec_CHC-1521">
        <num>CHC 1521</num>
        <heading>1521. Â Review; permanency planning</heading>
        <subsection eId="CHC-1521__subsec_A">
          <num>A.</num>
          <content>
            <p>On its own motion or on the motion of any party, the court may order a hearing to be set for review of the transfer of custody.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CHC-1521__subsec_B">
          <num>B.</num>
          <content>
            <p>Judgments transferring custody pursuant to this Chapter are exempt from the permanency planning requirements mandated in Title VI including the provisions of Chapters 13, 15 and 16 of that Title.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=72989</p>
        </authorialNote>
      </section>
